name: Austin Dantzler
text: If you have not tried it already, I have to give a reccomendation for the Papa Murphy's pizza next to Publix.  The thin crust is really good, but it is the stuffed pizza that is absolutely amazing!

name: Nikki Thompson
text: I know many people are used to take out that is hot at the door but I like the fact I can control whether my pizza is baked when and how I want it.  The staff is pleasant every time which is a plus always sure to greet me as soon as I enter.  Nice place and great food.  Worth trying it.

name: Kris Klenke
text: Best Pizza Ever!!!! I‚Äôve been cooking these pizza‚Äôs in Wisconsin since the late 90s and was glad to see them finally migrate south. You get so much more value then other pizza places and taste way better. I‚Äôd recommend the 5-meats stuffed pizza or if you don‚Äôt need that much the Chicken Garlic is great too.

name: John Y
text: Staff was super friendly. Stopped in after work and was in and out in about 10 minutes. Got home cooked up the pizza and was really surprised  how much better it was than the typical delivery/pick-up pizza options in the area. I will definitely  visit again.

name: Jarrett Glass
text: Being a native New Yorker I was very skeptical of this place, but I decided to go against my better judgement and give it a try. I'm glad I did because I was pleasantly surprised at how good it was. Since then I've tried a few different ‚Ä¶More

name: heather h
text: If you are looking for a place that has a good gluten free pizza... this is it. One of the best GF pizzas we've had. Staff is super friendly and our food is always good and ready on time. Great addition to the area...

name: Matt Harrell
text: Bought 2 pizzas after hearing a few folks rave about these pizzas for sometime.  Maybe my expectations were set too high.  My family and I found the pizza to be bland.  Very little sauce, and overall just a below average taste.  Save a couple of bucks and go elsewhere and get some flavor.

name: Sasha Henderson
text: Really good pizza! At first I was like who pays that much money to have to take it home and cook it! Lol it was well worth itüòçI will definitely become a regular here!

name: Evi Danaher
text: Staff is always very pleasant. Make you feel at home. They always go out of their way to make sure your pizza is exactly how you want it.

name: M Munge
text: Great pizza, fresh ingredients, and friendly staff. Taking it home to bake saves money and allows great customization of the pizza. This is becoming my preferred choice of pizza in the area.

name: Lori Reed
text: Really expensive for a cheese pizza that I had to bake myself.  Flavor was ok.  The cheese was fresh though.

name: lourdes thorn
text: Great product...fresh... easy to baked!!! Cheaper than other pizza joints and better!

name: Mike Seaborn
text: Love the $10 Tuesday. Can't beat it. Pizza is always fresh. Fun to watch them make it.

name: David Maillie
text: Twas good on a cold, snowy day. The place smells really good. Ask for bacon, sausage and extra cheese.

name: David Hill
text: Great for someone who doesn't want to wait for delivery, and still wants a convenient quick meal. The Mediterranean recipe is amazing!

name: Anne Brown
text: Very friendly workers and fast service. Good price and the pizza was delicious!

name: Elizabeth Syska
